  "normalization": "Executed-query mapping: the brief's frozen selection queries are `gh search code --filename '*.yml' --path '.github/workflows' '<TERM>' --limit 50` for TERM in ('uv run', 'uvx', 'run: pytest'). gh 2.96 has no --path flag and does not honor a '*.yml' --filename glob, so each was executed as the inline-qualifier form recorded in selection_queries (path:.github/workflows in the query, results post-filtered to paths ending .yml/.yaml). Query index 2 ('run: pytest') is retained verbatim but GitHub parses the colon as an unknown qualifier and returns zero results; per the task's documented latitude an analogous query index 3 ('run pytest') was appended to reach 20 blocks. Retrieval performed 2026-07-19.\nSelection rule: iterate each query's results in returned order; skip files without a pull_request or pull_request_target trigger, blocks longer than 40 lines, and repositories already selected; take the first 20 accepted run: blocks overall, at most one per repository. For a file with several run: steps, the mined block is the first run: step whose script invokes the query tool as a command. Each source is pinned to the latest commit that touched the file at retrieval; source_url is the https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/blob/{commit}/{path} permalink of the exact fetched version.\nSubstitution rule (mechanical; leaves every wild option, value, and all surrounding shell structure byte-identical): replace the invoked console-script / launcher-payload executable word with `doc-lattice` (in uvx / uv run / uv tool run forms also replace the --from distribution word when present, preserving any @spec or ==version suffix shape), and establish `check` as its subcommand. If the word immediately after the executable is a bare literal word (does not begin with `-`; no quoting, expansion, or glob) it occupied the subcommand position and is replaced by `check` (for example `ruff check .` becomes `doc-lattice check .`). Otherwise (the word immediately after the executable begins with `-`, or the executable has no following word) `check` is inserted immediately after the `doc-lattice` token and every wild option and value after it is kept byte-identical (for example `pytest --cov=src` becomes `doc-lattice check --cov=src`, `uvx diffoscope --html f a b` becomes `uvx doc-lattice check --html f a b`, and a bare `pytest` becomes `doc-lattice check`). A folded (>) run body is emitted as its folded single-line shell text under the literal (|) skeleton. Amended 2026-07-19 by project-owner adjudication from the earlier form that inserted no `check` when the invocation had no positional argument. Each fixture's expected_status, expected_invocations, and reason_category were derived independently by hand from the D2/D3 checklist of the 2026-07-19 allowlist-recognizer design spec, without running any scanner or parser on the fixtures.",
